trans-unit.source: Represents a subsection of a geometry, a single connected series of two-dimensional geometric segments.
A <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry> is made up of one or more figures, represented by the <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathFigure> class.
Each figure is itself made up of one or more segments, defined by the <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathSegment> class.
XAML Object Element Usage
XAML Values
One or more object elements for objects that derive from <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathSegment>.
Typically these are: <xref:System.Windows.Media.ArcSegment>,

<xref:System.Windows.Media.BezierSegment>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.LineSegment>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.PolyBezierSegment>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.PolyLineSegment>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.PolyQuadraticBezierSegment>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.QuadraticBezierSegment>.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> class.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> class with the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure.StartPoint"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure.Segments"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure.IsClosed"></xref> values.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure.StartPoint"></xref> for the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure.Segments"></xref> for the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure.IsClosed"></xref> for the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref>.
Creates a modifiable clone of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref>, making deep copies of this object's values.
When copying dependency properties, this method copies resource references and data bindings (but they might no longer resolve) but not animations or their current values.
This method is used to produce modifiable copies of frozen <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> objects (or any <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> object).
For convenience, this method shadows the inherited version with a strongly typed implementation.
For more information, see <xref:System.Windows.Freezable.Clone%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.
A modifiable clone of the current object.
The cloned object's <xref href="System.Windows.Freezable.IsFrozen"></xref> property will be `false` even if the source's <xref href="System.Windows.Freezable.IsFrozen"></xref> property was `true.`
Creates a modifiable clone of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> object, making deep copies of this object's current values.
Resource references, data bindings, and animations are not copied, but their current values are.
This method is used to produce modifiable copies of frozen <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> objects (or any <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> object).
For convenience, this method shadows the inherited version with a strongly typed implementation.
For more information, see <xref:System.Windows.Freezable.CloneCurrentValue%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.
A modifiable clone of the current object.
The cloned object's <xref href="System.Windows.Freezable.IsFrozen"></xref> property will be `false` even if the source's <xref href="System.Windows.Freezable.IsFrozen"></xref> property was `true`.
Gets a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> object that is an polygonal approximation of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> object.
The flattening process is lossy with respect to animation and curve segment parameters.
The polygonal approximation of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> object.

Gets a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> object, within the specified error of tolerance, that is an polygonal approximation of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> object.
The flattening process is lossy with respect to animation and curve segment parameters.
`tolerance` determines how closely the curve is approximated.
The computational tolerance of error.
Specifies how the error of tolerance is interpreted.
The polygonal approximation of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> object.
Gets or sets a value that specifies whether this figures first and last segments are connected.
Dependency Property Information
Identifier field
Metadata properties set to `true`
None
`true` if this figure's first and last segments are connected; otherwise, `false`.
The default value is `false`.
Identifies the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure.IsClosed"></xref> dependency property.
Gets or sets whether the contained area of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> is to be used for hit-testing, rendering, and clipping.

If this property is set to `false`, then only the outline of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathFigure> will be used, and its contained area will not contribute to the overall area of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathFigure>.
One use of this property is to allow unfilled strokes in an otherwise filled <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>, like the mouth in the left Smiley below.
Setting the mouth's <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathFigure.IsFilled%2A> to `true` may produce the undesired effect of the mouth in the right Smiley.
![smiley path is filled](~/add/media/ref-mil-pathfigure-isfilled-smiley.PNG "smiley path is filled")

Determines whether the contained area of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> is to be used for hit-testing, rendering, and clipping.

Determines whether this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> object may have curved segments.
`true` if this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> object may have curved segments; otherwise, `false`.
Gets or sets the collection of segments that define the shape of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.PathFigure"></xref> object.
